<br>
I don't know what your looking for but I think you'll be lucky to find it in any game.  <br>
<br>
I bet you if they came out and said &quot;we're going to make EQ a fully interactive virtual environment complete with 3D goggles and sensory equipment, photo-realistic graphics, complete voice/movment interface at no extra charge to you, the response would be: &quot;meh, I'd get goggle lines on my face&quot;.<br>
<br>
Sounds like you have already decided EQ will never improve, I don't see what posting here accomplishes.<br>
<br>
As for the 9th spell gem...woot! I'm always looking for one more song.  I won't give up my ornate greaves just because I don't want to have to devote a song gem to selos (that and I like the 1 second cast...another item I wish was inventory clickable.)<br>
<br>
More spell slots will be nice, but not as necessary.  I rarely have to click effects off, and when I do it's *normally* easy to decide.  Not bad though.<br>
<br>
Overall the expansion sounds solid enough, depending on the results of the content.<br>
<br>
